title: Lenore Taylor resigns as Guardian Australia editor after 10 years of leadership
summary_full: Australia’s longest-serving editor credited with transforming a fledgling news organisation into the fourth most-read news websiteGet our breaking news email, free app or daily news podcastGuardian Australia’s editor-in-chief, Lenore Taylor, has resigned after 10 years in the role, credited with taking the fledgling news organisation from a tiny startup to the fourth most-read news website in the country.Taylor joined the global media organisation Guardian News and Media in 2013 as founding political editor of the new Australian venture, rising to editor-in-chief in 2016.
